Now a days you uses framework for your project which has components and all. We have variable at component level and then that are bound to html.

    class component {
      constructor() {
       this.data  = {};
      }
      // lets say you bring data and have to assign to above this.data
      getData() {
        
          somePromise.then((res) =&gt; {
            this.data = res // you can access parent. No this dra,a
          })
      }     

     }

But in case of normal function


        
      getData() {
          const self = this; // save parent this to local variable
          somePromise.then(function(res) {
               self.data = res // now you can set data as function&#39;this is different here
          })
       }
    
There are other approach as well. You can bind your anonymous function with this using native bind function and then you can access valid **this** inside anonymous function.

So in real world, arrow function has solved this dilemma brilliantly.

